Package: zfsutils-linux
Section: contrib/admin
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: python3, ${misc:Depends}, ${python3:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: lsb-base, zfs-modules [amd64 arm64 ppc64el s390x] | zfs-dkms [amd64 arm64 ppc64el s390x], zfs-zed
Breaks: zfs-dkms (<< ${binary:Version}), zfs-dkms (>> ${binary:Version})
Suggests: nfs-kernel-server,
          samba-common-bin (>= 3.0.23),
          zfs-modules [armhf i386] | zfs-dkms [armhf i386],
          zfs-initramfs | zfs-dracut
Conflicts: zfs, zfs-fuse
Provides: zfsutils
Description: command-line tools to manage OpenZFS filesystems
 The Z file system is a pooled filesystem designed for maximum data
 integrity, supporting data snapshots, multiple copies, and data
 checksums.
 .
 This package provides the zfs and zpool commands to create and administer
 OpenZFS filesystems.

